# Requester Read — Select Hydrate

Authoritative contract: `docs/platforms/backend/patterns/requester-read-select-hydrate.md`.

## Rule

When `read` values hydrate website `FormChoiceField` or `FormEntityPickerField`:

| Kind | Required |
|---|---|
| Domain enum | `await this.toEnumForSelect(value, enumKey)` |
| Related entity | `related?.forSelect(this.context.lang()) ?? null` |

`ReadResult` types those fields as `SelectOption` (or `Nullable<SelectOption>`).

## Model `forSelect`

- Per related model instance method — **not** a generic Model base.
- Return `{ value: id, label: display }`; keep `lang` param for multilang labels.

## Forbidden

- Bare enum string or bare FK id for choice/picker-bound `read` fields.
- Hand-built `{ value, label }` in the requester when `toEnumForSelect` / `forSelect` already covers it.
- Echoing the edited entity id in `read` values (see `requester-read-no-entity-id-echo.mdc`).

## Write path unchanged

Creates/updates still use `joi.select({ validValues })` / Opt helpers. Do not require SelectOption-only writes.
